---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Process - Anastasia Bessonova"
  description="Narrative design process - from discovery to implementation."
>
  <section class="card">
    <h1>Process</h1>
    <p>
      How I approach narrative design - from early discovery to implementation
      and iteration within production constraints.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section card">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">1) Discovery</h2>
    <p>
      Understanding goals, audience, constraints, tone, references, and the role
      of narrative within the wider design and production context.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section card">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">2) Structure</h2>
    <p>
      Defining narrative pillars, beats, pacing, character arcs, and branching
      logic when interactivity is involved.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section card">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">3) Writing</h2>
    <p>
      Writing dialogue, barks, item text, cutscenes, cinematics, and VO notes with
      clarity, consistency, and production awareness.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section card">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">4) Implementation</h2>
    <p>
      Translating narrative into engine-ready content using tools, variables,
      conditions, flags, and close collaboration with design and engineering.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section card">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">5) Iteration</h2>
    <p>
      Testing, feedback loops, rewrites, and polish passes to improve clarity,
      pacing, and player experience.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
